Here's how you can modify the Python code to include the specified headers:

```python
import requests
import base64

# Encode the SonarQube token to base64
sonarwube_token = "YOUR_SONARWUBE_TOKEN_HERE"
encoded_token = base64.b64encode(sonarwube_token.encode()).decode()

url = "https://abc.sonar.def.com/api/issues/do_transition"
data = {
    "issue": "jsjsjjsjsjdjd",
    "transition": "confirm"
}
headers = {
    "Authorization": "Basic " + encoded_token,
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Content-Type": "application/json"
}

response = requests.post(url, json=data, headers=headers)

print(response.text)
```

Replace `"YOUR_SONARWUBE_TOKEN_HERE"` with your actual SonarQube token. This code will encode the token to base64, then send a POST request with the provided data and include the specified headers.